Package: tihoCluster
Title: Unsupervised Cluster analysis (Kmeans) for the automation of the categorization task. The model automatically finds an optimal number of clusters (e.g., call types) in the data. 
Version: 1.0
Date: 24-05-2023
Authors@R: 
    person("Daniel", "Romero-Mujalli", "danielrm84@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "danielrm84@gmail.com")
Author: Daniel Romero-Mujalli [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Daniel Romero-Mujalli <danielrm84@gmail.com>
Description: This function performs unsupervised clustering using the K-means model. The optimal number of clusters is selected automatically according to two alternative methods decided by the user: i) Silhouette score, (ii) Knee method (based on Coffey et al. 2019, Neuropsychopharmacology, 44(5): 859-868).
License: `use_mit_license()`
URL: https://github.com/danielrm84/tihoCluster
BugReports: https://github.com/danielrm84/tihoCluster/issues
